00:36:02.650 --> 00:36:05.220
But no, we never went
out of our way.

00:36:05.220 --> 00:36:09.288
AUDIENCE: What stopped you from
putting on red lipstick?

00:36:09.288 --> 00:36:11.290
STEPHEN PEARCY: I wasn't
attracted to dudes.

00:36:11.290 --> 00:36:12.684
I don't know.

00:36:15.400 --> 00:36:15.830
No.

00:36:15.830 --> 00:36:19.040
You know, the '80s were
an interesting thing.

00:36:19.040 --> 00:36:21.180
You've got to understand
it was all new.

00:36:21.180 --> 00:36:25.260
So it wasn't us, like when
people tell me, oh, what

00:36:25.260 --> 00:36:27.750
killed the '80s, whatever.

00:36:27.750 --> 00:36:30.030
It's like, it wasn't us.

00:36:30.030 --> 00:36:33.520
And maybe it was those bands
that came after as that were

00:36:33.520 --> 00:36:36.800
cookie-cutter bands.

00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:39.180
You had all these goofy-ass
bands that came out of

00:36:39.180 --> 00:36:44.610
nowhere, and they'd just poof
them all up and find out who

00:36:44.610 --> 00:36:47.540
may our clothes.

00:36:47.540 --> 00:36:51.680
But we're still standing.

00:36:51.680 --> 00:36:55.310
If you've been standing for
over 20 years, you've got

00:36:55.310 --> 00:36:56.490
something going for you.

00:36:56.490 --> 00:37:00.660
We'll be 30 years next year.

00:37:00.660 --> 00:37:01.630
KATE MACEVICZ: Congrats.

00:37:01.630 --> 00:37:03.460
Yeah.

00:37:03.460 --> 00:37:04.765
STEPHEN PEARCY: It's
interesting.

00:37:04.765 --> 00:37:06.490
